				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2633474#post-4287093</guid>
				<title>If I understand this right (and I definitely don&#039;t)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2633474/scp-3443#post-4287093</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2019 05:48:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Anitar</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2108007</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;O5-███&quot; (with <em>three</em> blackboxes) is nothing more than an agent of this hypothetical instance of SCP-3443. As such, they have a vested interest in <em>making sure</em> you figure out what's going on (while still maintaining plausible deniability). That's how they spread the cognitohazard. So the part that you dislike is more or less <em>necessitated</em> by the circumstances.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
