					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2633474#post-3593995</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2633474/scp-3443#post-3593995</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 15 Sep 2017 20:12:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Ferociousfeind</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3184300</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's somewhat similar SCP to 55, but how it goes about it's antimemetics is different. Instead of erasing the knowledge from your mind, it assures you that it's an example and it doesn't actually exist. Which is why the Foundation <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">is</span> was having so much trouble with linked accounts being corrupted. The SCP's &quot;nonexistence&quot; is extending from this entry across links to erase and/or corrupt files ad infinitum.<br /> Or something. It's hard to tell with all these tricky series IV's.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
